        <section id="parts">
            <h2>Essential Parts</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>CPU (Processor)</li>
                <li>Motherboard</li>
                <li>RAM (Memory)</li>
                <li>GPU (Graphics Card)</li>
                <li>Storage (SSD/HDD)</li>
                <li>Power Supply (PSU)</li>
                <li>Case</li>
                <li>Cooling (Fans or Liquid Cooling)</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="steps">
            <h2>Basic Build Steps</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Install the CPU and cooler on the motherboard.</li>
                <li>Install RAM onto the motherboard.</li>
                <li>Mount the motherboard into the case.</li>
                <li>Install the power supply.</li>
                <li>Connect storage drives.</li>
                <li>Install the graphics card.</li>
                <li>Connect all power and data cables.</li>
                <li>Double-check connections and power it on!</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section id="tips">
            <h2>Quick Tips</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Always ground yourself to prevent static damage.</li>
                <li>Use a good quality power supply — don't skimp!</li>
                <li>Make sure your parts are compatible.</li>
                <li>Take your time — rushing can cause mistakes.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
